<h1>@HI{{kashira}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @Vru{{}} <strong>@HI{{kashira}}</strong>.
<li> @Ai{{}} <strong>@HI{{kashira}}</strong>.
<li> @Anastem{{}} <strong>@HI{{kashira}}</strong>.
<li> @N{{}} <strong>@HI{{kashira}}</strong>.
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{kashira}}</strong> is a sentence ending particle mainly used by women and usually is translated as "I wonder".
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{kashira}}</strong> can indicate uncertainty

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono@KJ{{mechanism^contraption}}no@KJ{{use}}i@KJ{{direction}},go@KJ{{exist}}deirasshaimasu<strong>kashira</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I wonder if you are aquainted with how this machine works?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{kashira}}</strong> can mark a question to oneself

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{mou@KJ{{homecoming}}ttemoiino<strong>kashira</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I wonder if it's OK if I leave now?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{kashira}}</strong> can indicate a hope or a muted request

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{konpyu-ta-}}no@KJ{{use}}i@KJ{{direction}},@KJ{{teach}}eteitadakeru<strong>kashira</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I wonder if you could teach me how to operate this computer?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
The equivalent male particle is <a href="grammar-particle-kana.html">@HI{{kana}}</a>.
<p>

